<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-EVSTQN3/azprG1Anm3QDgpJLIm9Nao0Yz1ztcQTwFspd3yD65VohhpuuCOmLASjC" crossorigin="anonymous">

<head>
  <title>Rails Blog</title>
</head>

<br>
<body style="background-color:#D4F5F5;">
  <div class="container">

    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
      <ol class="breadcrumb">
        <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Home</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="display-1">Blog with Rails! - Eric Bollar</h1>

    <h1 class="display-6">Home - All Articles</h1>

    <p class="lead" style="width: 80%;">This is a tech demonstration of Ruby on Rails where users can create/edit/delete articles as well as post comments.
    To find out more information, here is the link to the project <a href="https://github.com/EricBollar/RailsBlog">Github</a> and <a href="https://www.ericbollar.com">my website</a>. If you want to create an article of your own, the username
    and password are "dhh" and "secret" respectively. Articles must be at least 10 characters long. Feel free to comment on an article!</p>

    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="window.location.href='<%= new_article_path %>';">Create Article</button>
    There are <strong><%= Article.public_count %></strong> articles currently!

    <ul>
      <br>
      <% @articles.each do |article| %>
        <% unless article.archived? %>
          <li>
            <%= link_to article.title, article %>
          </li>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
